I am a black American, the great-grandchild of those born into enslavement and raised by those for whom Jim Crow was not history. This song, Freedom, resonates with me on an ancestral level: the gospel inflections, the drums, the liberatory dance (including circle dance, with its African origins), the beat----and the themes "freedom and transcendence" goes to the heart of the black experience. I am reminded of the spirituals, and every other musical form that grew out of black pain, suffering, and joy. â€œFeel my freedom; feel my freedom, freedomâ€ (call and response). â€œFeel my rhythm, rhythm (divinely).â€  This is the inheritance, a freedom no one can take, that I seek for my son, as did all those black folk who came before me on American soil.  Say it, one more time to the heavens: Freedom, Freedom, Freedom!
